In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin. Stir in the chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees F for 9-12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks.